cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a new channel attention mechanism for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to improve performance in visual tasks. As such, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a probabilistic interpretation of the channel attention mechanism, which suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Gaussian processes also suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the experimental results involve image classification, which suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
